<paragraph base="SL30064" principles="yes" id="IAS12_71"><paranum>71</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IAS 12"/><data name="paranum" value="71"/></prolog><body><p id="IAS12_P0411">An entity shall offset <xref base="SL143755" href="IAS12_5.dita#IAS12_5/IAS12_P0020">current tax<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0069"/></ph></xref> assets and current tax liabilities if, and only if, the entity: </p><ol base="SL143989" type="lower-alpha" id="IAS12_L0037"><li><li_value>(a)</li_value>         <p base="SL143991" id="IAS12_P0412">has a legally enforceable right to set off the recognised amounts; and</p>       </li><li><li_value>(b)</li_value>         <p base="SL143993" id="IAS12_P0413">intends either to settle on a net basis, or to realise the asset and settle the liability simultaneously.</p>       </li></ol></body></paragraph>